propertyDetails.description:
The Sapphire is a luxurious beachfront resort offering breathtaking views of the Indian Ocean and direct access to pristine sands. Free WiFi access is available in all rooms. Staff can converse in French, Portuguese, and Chinese.

Featuring private sundecks and balconies, large villas are decorated with fine wood furnishings and warm colors. The property features elegantly designed Portuguese-style rooms, exquisite dining options, a rejuvenating spa, and a variety of wellness activities, including Yoga, Sculpting, and Sound Therapy. Premium toiletries and rain showers are provided.  Extras in the room include a dental kit and slippers. A wide range of water sports including diving, fishing, and windsurfing are available at the Sapphire Hotel and Resorts, Seychelles. Snorkeling and scuba diving can be arranged upon request. Alternatively, relax with soothing spa treatments at Amethyst Spa. All-day dining with a wide spread of international dishes is provided at 80 Degrees Restaurant.

Sapphire Hotel and Resorts, Seychelles, is 8 km from Seychelles International Airport, which takes 15 minutes by a private speedboat available 24 hours a day.

propertyDetails.description:
Nestled in the picturesque countryside just outside the town of Vík, Hotel Katla is a 103-room country hotel situated 5 km east of Vík, on the south coast. A family-run gem on Iceland’s stunning south coast,  it boasts of majestic glaciers serving as a breathtaking backdrop. Since its inception in 1988 as a farmhouse accommodation, the hotel has evolved to cater primarily to group travel, with about 65% of its guests arriving through domestic and international travel agencies. 

The area's natural beauty has attracted various advertising and film projects, further enhancing its appeal. The hotel benefits from its own geothermal heating utility and storage tank, ensuring a sustainable and efficient energy supply.

Guests can enjoy all-day dining in a large dining hall that comfortably seats up to 250 people. For business and events, the hotel features a well-equipped conference room with a stage, accommodating up to 80 attendees. The central reception area includes a bar offering a variety of drinks and retail items. For relaxation, the outdoor area boasts a hot tub and sauna, perfect for unwinding amidst the natural beauty. 

Hotel Katla is not just a place to stay; it's a destination where guests can immerse themselves in Iceland’s natural wonders while enjoying modern comforts and amenities.
